<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910913-0175</DOCNO><DOCID>910913-0175.</DOCID><HL>   Credit Ratings:   Massachusetts Bond Rating</HL><DATE>09/13/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C14</SO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)STOCK AND BOND RATINGS (RTG)</IN><NS>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)BOND andamp; STOCK RATINGS (RTG)</NS><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- Standard andamp; Poor's Corp., sayingMassachusetts's fiscal outlook has stabilized, reaffirmed thestate's lowest-in-the-country triple-B rating.   Previously, the ratings agency judged the fiscal outlook&quot;negative,&quot; indicating downgrades were possible. Aspokeswoman said the agency no long expects furtherdowngrades. The rating covers $6 billion of generalobligation bonds.</LP><TEXT>   Sandamp;P cited improved cooperation between the governor andstate legislators, conservative revenue estimates andimproved budget procedures. In July and August, tax revenueexceeded estimates.   Sandamp;P said it isn't ready to raise the rating, however,because the current budget is balanced with the aid of about$1 billion in &quot;one-shot revenues.&quot; It warned of greaterfiscal pressures next year when such revenues are no longeravailable.</TEXT></DOC>